The paper deals with the classification of malware types using machine learning and deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also mentions the use of ensemble models and bootstrap aggregating technique, which are commonly used in machine learning and deep learning. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
